The Java class library ID OBIDISC4J from FEIG ELECTRONIC GmbH represents yet another component for simplifying the development of application programs in Java for OBID i-scan® and OBID® classic-pro readers.
The Java class library ID OBIDISC4J currently supports 32- and 64-Bit Windows and 32- and 64-Bit Linux with installed 32-Bit or 64-Bit Java Runtime Environment (JRE) 5 or higher and Android, beginning with 4.0.3 (Ice Cream Sandwich).
The Java class library ID OBIDISC4J is based on the C++ class library FEDM as well as the native function libraries FECOM, FEUSB, FETCP, FEISC, FEFU and FETCL. The Java class library therefore consists only of a wrapper. Nevertheless, the full functionality of the C++ class library is accessible for Java:
- A uniform organizational principle for savable data from reader and transponder in data containers and tables.
- Overloaded methods for access to the data containers and tables.
- Unified namespaces for all configuration parameters of all readers.
- A single, easy to use communications method.
- Synchronous and asynchronous communication
- Complete error handling using exceptions or return values from methods.
- A simple way of serializing reader configuration data in an XML file.

For more general information, please refer to the manual H31101-xe-ID-B.doc
